58Group::Group() : m_leaderGuid(), m_leaderName(""), m_groupType(GROUPTYPE_NORMAL),
59m_dungeonDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_NORMAL), m_raidDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_NORMAL_RAID), m_legacyRaidDifficulty(DIFFICULTY_10_N),
60m_bgGroup(nullptr), m_bfGroup(nullptr), m_lootMethod(FREE_FOR_ALL), m_lootThreshold(ITEM_QUALITY_UNCOMMON), m_looterGuid(),
61m_masterLooterGuid(), m_subGroupsCounts(nullptr), m_guid(), m_counter(0), m_maxEnchantingLevel(0), m_dbStoreId(0),
62m_readyCheckStarted(false), m_readyCheckTimer(0), m_activeMarkers(0)
63{
64 for (uint8 i = 0; i < TARGET_ICONS_COUNT; ++i)
65 m_targetIcons[i].Clear();
66
67 for (uint8 i = 0; i < RAID_MARKERS_COUNT; ++i)
68 m_markers[i] = nullptr;
69}
70
71Group::~Group()
72{
73 if (m_bgGroup)
74 {
75 TC_LOG_DEBUG("bg.battleground", "Group::~Group: battleground group being deleted.");
76 if (m_bgGroup->GetBgRaid(ALLIANCE) == this) m_bgGroup->SetBgRaid(ALLIANCE, NULL);
77 else if (m_bgGroup->GetBgRaid(HORDE) == this) m_bgGroup->SetBgRaid(HORDE, NULL);
78 else TC_LOG_ERROR("misc", "Group::~Group: battleground group is not linked to the correct battleground.");
79 }
80 Rolls::iterator itr;
81 while (!RollId.empty())
82 {
83 itr = RollId.begin();
84 Roll *r = *itr;
85 RollId.erase(itr);
86 delete(r);
87 }
88
89 // this may unload some instance saves
90 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_DIFFICULTY; ++i)
91 for (BoundInstancesMap::iterator itr2 = m_boundInstances[i].begin(); itr2 != m_boundInstances[i].end(); ++itr2)
92 itr2->second.save->RemoveGroup(this);
93
94 // Sub group counters clean up
95 delete[] m_subGroupsCounts;
96}

98bool Group::Create(Player* leader)
99{
100 ObjectGuid leaderGuid = leader->GetGUID();
101
102 m_guid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Party>(sGroupMgr->GenerateGroupId());
103 m_leaderGuid = leaderGuid;
104 m_leaderName = leader->GetName();
105 leader->SetFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GROUP_LEADER);
106
107 if (isBGGroup() || isBFGroup())
108 m_groupType = GROUPTYPE_BGRAID;
109
110 if (m_groupType & GROUPTYPE_RAID)
111 _initRaidSubGroupsCounter();
112
113 if (!isLFGGroup())
114 m_lootMethod = GROUP_LOOT;
115
116 m_lootThreshold = ITEM_QUALITY_UNCOMMON;
117 m_looterGuid = leaderGuid;
118 m_masterLooterGuid.Clear();
119
120 m_dungeonDifficulty = DIFFICULTY_NORMAL;
121 m_raidDifficulty = DIFFICULTY_NORMAL_RAID;
122 m_legacyRaidDifficulty = DIFFICULTY_10_N;
123
124 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
125 {
126 m_dungeonDifficulty = leader->GetDungeonDifficultyID();
127 m_raidDifficulty = leader->GetRaidDifficultyID();
128 m_legacyRaidDifficulty = leader->GetLegacyRaidDifficultyID();
129
130 m_dbStoreId = sGroupMgr->GenerateNewGroupDbStoreId();
131
132 sGroupMgr->RegisterGroupDbStoreId(m_dbStoreId, this);
133
134 // Store group in database
135 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GROUP);
136
137 uint8 index = 0;
138
139 stmt->setUInt32(index++, m_dbStoreId);
140 stmt->setUInt64(index++, m_leaderGuid.GetCounter());
141 stmt->setUInt8(index++, uint8(m_lootMethod));
142 stmt->setUInt64(index++, m_looterGuid.GetCounter());
143 stmt->setUInt8(index++, uint8(m_lootThreshold));
144 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[0].GetRawValue());
145 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[1].GetRawValue());
146 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[2].GetRawValue());
147 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[3].GetRawValue());
148 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[4].GetRawValue());
149 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[5].GetRawValue());
150 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[6].GetRawValue());
151 stmt->setBinary(index++, m_targetIcons[7].GetRawValue());
152 stmt->setUInt8(index++, uint8(m_groupType));
153 stmt->setUInt32(index++, uint8(m_dungeonDifficulty));
154 stmt->setUInt32(index++, uint8(m_raidDifficulty));
155 stmt->setUInt32(index++, uint8(m_legacyRaidDifficulty));
156 stmt->setUInt64(index++, m_masterLooterGuid.GetCounter());
157
158 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
159
160
161 ASSERT(AddMember(leader)); // If the leader can't be added to a new group because it appears full, something is clearly wrong.
162
163 Player::ConvertInstancesToGroup(leader, this, false);
164 }
165 else if (!AddMember(leader))
166 return false;
167
168 return true;
169}

171void Group::LoadGroupFromDB(Field* fields)
172{
173 m_dbStoreId = fields[17].GetUInt32();
174 m_guid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Party>(sGroupMgr->GenerateGroupId());
175 m_leaderGuid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Player>(fields[0].GetUInt64());
176
177 // group leader not exist
178 if (!ObjectMgr::GetPlayerNameByGUID(m_leaderGuid, m_leaderName))
179 return;
180
181 m_lootMethod = LootMethod(fields[1].GetUInt8());
182 m_looterGuid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Player>(fields[2].GetUInt64());
183 m_lootThreshold = ItemQualities(fields[3].GetUInt8());
184
185 for (uint8 i = 0; i < TARGET_ICONS_COUNT; ++i)
186 m_targetIcons[i].SetRawValue(fields[4 + i].GetBinary());
187
188 m_groupType = GroupType(fields[12].GetUInt8());
189 if (m_groupType & GROUPTYPE_RAID)
190 _initRaidSubGroupsCounter();
191
192 m_dungeonDifficulty = Player::CheckLoadedDungeonDifficultyID(Difficulty(fields[13].GetUInt8()));
193 m_raidDifficulty = Player::CheckLoadedRaidDifficultyID(Difficulty(fields[14].GetUInt8()));
194 m_legacyRaidDifficulty = Player::CheckLoadedLegacyRaidDifficultyID(Difficulty(fields[15].GetUInt8()));
195
196 m_masterLooterGuid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Player>(fields[16].GetUInt64());
197
198 if (m_groupType & GROUPTYPE_LFG)
199 sLFGMgr->_LoadFromDB(fields, GetGUID());
200}

202void Group::LoadMemberFromDB(ObjectGuid::LowType guidLow, uint8 memberFlags, uint8 subgroup, uint8 roles)
203{
204 MemberSlot member;
205 member.guid = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Player>(guidLow);
206
207 // skip non-existed member
208 if (!ObjectMgr::GetPlayerNameAndClassByGUID(member.guid, member.name, member._class))
209 {
210 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP_MEMBER);
211 stmt->setUInt64(0, guidLow);
212 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
213 return;
214 }
215
216 member.group = subgroup;
217 member.flags = memberFlags;
218 member.roles = roles;
219 member.readyChecked = false;
220
221 m_memberSlots.push_back(member);
222
223 SubGroupCounterIncrease(subgroup);
224
225 sLFGMgr->SetupGroupMember(member.guid, GetGUID());
226}

228void Group::ConvertToLFG()
229{
230 m_groupType = GroupType(m_groupType | GROUPTYPE_LFG | GROUPTYPE_LFG_RESTRICTED);
231 m_lootMethod = NEED_BEFORE_GREED;
232 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
233 {
234 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_TYPE);
235
236 stmt->setUInt8(0, uint8(m_groupType));
237 stmt->setUInt32(1, m_dbStoreId);
238
239 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
240 }
241
242 SendUpdate();
243}
244
245void Group::ConvertToRaid()
246{
247 m_groupType = GroupType(m_groupType | GROUPTYPE_RAID);
248
249 _initRaidSubGroupsCounter();
250
251 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
252 {
253 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_TYPE);
254
255 stmt->setUInt8(0, uint8(m_groupType));
256 stmt->setUInt32(1, m_dbStoreId);
257
258 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
259 }
260
261 SendUpdate();
262
263 // update quest related GO states (quest activity dependent from raid membership)
264 for (member_citerator citr = m_memberSlots.begin(); citr != m_memberSlots.end(); ++citr)
265 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(citr->guid))
266 player->UpdateForQuestWorldObjects();
267}
268
269void Group::ConvertToGroup()
270{
271 if (m_memberSlots.size() > 5)
272 return; // What message error should we send?
273
274 m_groupType = GroupType(GROUPTYPE_NORMAL);
275
276 if (m_subGroupsCounts)
277 {
278 delete[] m_subGroupsCounts;
279 m_subGroupsCounts = NULL;
280 }
281
282 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
283 {
284 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_TYPE);
285
286 stmt->setUInt8(0, uint8(m_groupType));
287 stmt->setUInt32(1, m_dbStoreId);
288
289 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
290 }
291
292 SendUpdate();
293
294 // update quest related GO states (quest activity dependent from raid membership)
295 for (member_citerator citr = m_memberSlots.begin(); citr != m_memberSlots.end(); ++citr)
296 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(citr->guid))
297 player->UpdateForQuestWorldObjects();
298}

300bool Group::AddInvite(Player* player)
301{
302 if (!player || player->GetGroupInvite())
303 return false;
304 Group* group = player->GetGroup();
305 if (group && (group->isBGGroup() || group->isBFGroup()))
306 group = player->GetOriginalGroup();
307 if (group)
308 return false;
309
310 RemoveInvite(player);
311
312 m_invitees.insert(player);
313
314 player->SetGroupInvite(this);
315
316 sScriptMgr->OnGroupInviteMember(this, player->GetGUID());
317
318 return true;
319}
320
321bool Group::AddLeaderInvite(Player* player)
322{
323 if (!AddInvite(player))
324 return false;
325
326 m_leaderGuid = player->GetGUID();
327 m_leaderName = player->GetName();
328 return true;
329}

331void Group::RemoveInvite(Player* player)

336 player->SetGroupInvite(NULL);
337 }

340void Group::RemoveAllInvites()
341{
342 for (InvitesList::iterator itr=m_invitees.begin(); itr != m_invitees.end(); ++itr)
343 if (*itr)
344 (*itr)->SetGroupInvite(NULL);
345
346 m_invitees.clear();

349Player* Group::GetInvited(ObjectGuid guid) const
350{
351 for (InvitesList::const_iterator itr = m_invitees.begin(); itr != m_invitees.end(); ++itr)
352 {

369bool Group::AddMember(Player* player)
370{
371 // Get first not-full group
372 uint8 subGroup = 0;
373 if (m_subGroupsCounts)
374 {
375 bool groupFound = false;
376 for (; subGroup < MAX_RAID_SUBGROUPS; ++subGroup)
377 {
378 if (m_subGroupsCounts[subGroup] < MAX_GROUP_SIZE)
379 {
380 groupFound = true;
381 break;
382 }
383 }
384 // We are raid group and no one slot is free
385 if (!groupFound)
386 return false;
387 }
388
389 MemberSlot member;
390 member.guid = player->GetGUID();
391 member.name = player->GetName();
392 member._class = player->getClass();
393 member.group = subGroup;
394 member.flags = 0;
395 member.roles = 0;
396 member.readyChecked = false;
397 m_memberSlots.push_back(member);
398
399 SubGroupCounterIncrease(subGroup);
400
401 player->SetGroupInvite(NULL);
402 if (player->GetGroup())
403 {
404 if (isBGGroup() || isBFGroup()) // if player is in group and he is being added to BG raid group, then call SetBattlegroundRaid()
405 player->SetBattlegroundOrBattlefieldRaid(this, subGroup);
406 else //if player is in bg raid and we are adding him to normal group, then call SetOriginalGroup()
407 player->SetOriginalGroup(this, subGroup);
408 }
409 else //if player is not in group, then call set group
410 player->SetGroup(this, subGroup);
411
412 // if the same group invites the player back, cancel the homebind timer
413 InstanceGroupBind* bind = GetBoundInstance(player);
414 if (bind && bind->save->GetInstanceId() == player->GetInstanceId())
415 player->m_InstanceValid = true;
416
417 if (!isRaidGroup()) // reset targetIcons for non-raid-groups
418 {
419 for (uint8 i = 0; i < TARGET_ICONS_COUNT; ++i)
420 m_targetIcons[i].Clear();
421 }
422
423 // insert into the table if we're not a battleground group
424 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
425 {
426 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GROUP_MEMBER);
427
428 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
429 stmt->setUInt64(1, member.guid.GetCounter());
430 stmt->setUInt8(2, member.flags);
431 stmt->setUInt8(3, member.group);
432 stmt->setUInt8(4, member.roles);
433
434 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
435 }
436
437 SendUpdate();
438 sScriptMgr->OnGroupAddMember(this, player->GetGUID());
439
440 if (!IsLeader(player->GetGUID()) && !isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
441 {
442 // reset the new member's instances, unless he is currently in one of them
443 // including raid/heroic instances that they are not permanently bound to!
444 player->ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_JOIN, false, false);
445 player->ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_JOIN, true, false);
446 player->ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_JOIN, true, true);
447
448 if (player->getLevel() >= LEVELREQUIREMENT_HEROIC)
449 {
450 if (player->GetDungeonDifficultyID() != GetDungeonDifficultyID())
451 {
452 player->SetDungeonDifficultyID(GetDungeonDifficultyID());
453 player->SendDungeonDifficulty();
454 }
455 if (player->GetRaidDifficultyID() != GetRaidDifficultyID())
456 {
457 player->SetRaidDifficultyID(GetRaidDifficultyID());
458 player->SendRaidDifficulty(false);
459 }
460 if (player->GetLegacyRaidDifficultyID() != GetLegacyRaidDifficultyID())
461 {
462 player->SetLegacyRaidDifficultyID(GetLegacyRaidDifficultyID());
463 player->SendRaidDifficulty(true);
464 }
465 }
466 }
467
468 player->SetGroupUpdateFlag(GROUP_UPDATE_FULL);
469 if (Pet* pet = player->GetPet())
470 pet->SetGroupUpdateFlag(GROUP_UPDATE_PET_FULL);
471
472 UpdatePlayerOutOfRange(player);
473
474 // quest related GO state dependent from raid membership
475 if (isRaidGroup())
476 player->UpdateForQuestWorldObjects();
477
478 {
479 // Broadcast new player group member fields to rest of the group
480 player->SetFieldNotifyFlag(UF_FLAG_PARTY_MEMBER);
481
482 UpdateData groupData(player->GetMapId());
483 WorldPacket groupDataPacket;
484
485 // Broadcast group members' fields to player
486 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
487 {
488 if (itr->GetSource() == player)
489 continue;
490
491 if (Player* existingMember = itr->GetSource())
492 {
493 if (player->HaveAtClient(existingMember))
494 {
495 existingMember->SetFieldNotifyFlag(UF_FLAG_PARTY_MEMBER);
496 existingMember->BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer(&groupData, player);
497 existingMember->RemoveFieldNotifyFlag(UF_FLAG_PARTY_MEMBER);
498 }
499
500 if (existingMember->HaveAtClient(player))
501 {
502 UpdateData newData(player->GetMapId());
503 WorldPacket newDataPacket;
504 player->BuildValuesUpdateBlockForPlayer(&newData, existingMember);
505 if (newData.HasData())
506 {
507 newData.BuildPacket(&newDataPacket);
508 existingMember->SendDirectMessage(&newDataPacket);
509 }
510 }
511 }
512 }
513
514 if (groupData.HasData())
515 {
516 groupData.BuildPacket(&groupDataPacket);
517 player->SendDirectMessage(&groupDataPacket);
518 }
519
520 player->RemoveFieldNotifyFlag(UF_FLAG_PARTY_MEMBER);
521 }
522
523 if (m_maxEnchantingLevel < player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
524 m_maxEnchantingLevel = player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENCHANTING);
525
526 return true;
527}
528
529bool Group::RemoveMember(ObjectGuid guid, const RemoveMethod& method /*= GROUP_REMOVEMETHOD_DEFAULT*/, ObjectGuid kicker /*= 0*/, const char* reason /*= NULL*/)
530{
531 BroadcastGroupUpdate();
532
533 sScriptMgr->OnGroupRemoveMember(this, guid, method, kicker, reason);
534
535 // LFG group vote kick handled in scripts
536 if (isLFGGroup() && method == GROUP_REMOVEMETHOD_KICK)
537 return !m_memberSlots.empty();
538
539 // remove member and change leader (if need) only if strong more 2 members _before_ member remove (BG/BF allow 1 member group)
540 if (GetMembersCount() > ((isBGGroup() || isLFGGroup() || isBFGroup()) ? 1u : 2u))
541 {
542 Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(guid);
543 if (player)
544 {
545 // Battleground group handling
546 if (isBGGroup() || isBFGroup())
547 player->RemoveFromBattlegroundOrBattlefieldRaid();
548 else
549 // Regular group
550 {
551 if (player->GetOriginalGroup() == this)
552 player->SetOriginalGroup(NULL);
553 else
554 player->SetGroup(NULL);
555
556 // quest related GO state dependent from raid membership
557 player->UpdateForQuestWorldObjects();
558 }
559
560 WorldPacket data;
561
562 if (method == GROUP_REMOVEMETHOD_KICK || method == GROUP_REMOVEMETHOD_KICK_LFG)
563 {
564 data.Initialize(SMSG_GROUP_UNINVITE, 0);
565 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
566 }
567
568 _homebindIfInstance(player);
569 }
570
571 // Remove player from group in DB
572 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
573 {
574 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP_MEMBER);
575 stmt->setUInt64(0, guid.GetCounter());
576 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
577 DelinkMember(guid);
578 }
579
580 // Reevaluate group enchanter if the leaving player had enchanting skill or the player is offline
581 if (!player || player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
582 ResetMaxEnchantingLevel();
583
584 // Remove player from loot rolls
585 for (Rolls::iterator it = RollId.begin(); it != RollId.end(); ++it)
586 {
587 Roll* roll = *it;
588 Roll::PlayerVote::iterator itr2 = roll->playerVote.find(guid);
589 if (itr2 == roll->playerVote.end())
590 continue;
591
592 if (itr2->second == GREED || itr2->second == DISENCHANT)
593 --roll->totalGreed;
594 else if (itr2->second == NEED)
595 --roll->totalNeed;
596 else if (itr2->second == PASS)
597 --roll->totalPass;
598
599 if (itr2->second != NOT_VALID)
600 --roll->totalPlayersRolling;
601
602 roll->playerVote.erase(itr2);
603
604 CountRollVote(guid, roll->itemGUID, MAX_ROLL_TYPE);
605 }
606
607 // Update subgroups
608 member_witerator slot = _getMemberWSlot(guid);
609 if (slot != m_memberSlots.end())
610 {
611 SubGroupCounterDecrease(slot->group);
612 m_memberSlots.erase(slot);
613 }
614
615 // Pick new leader if necessary
616 if (m_leaderGuid == guid)
617 {
618 for (member_witerator itr = m_memberSlots.begin(); itr != m_memberSlots.end(); ++itr)
619 {
620 if (ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(itr->guid))
621 {
622 ChangeLeader(itr->guid);
623 break;
624 }
625 }
626 }
627
628 SendUpdate();
629
630 if (isLFGGroup() && GetMembersCount() == 1)
631 {
632 Player* leader = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(GetLeaderGUID());
633 uint32 mapId = sLFGMgr->GetDungeonMapId(GetGUID());
634 if (!mapId || !leader || (leader->IsAlive() && leader->GetMapId() != mapId))
635 {
636 Disband();
637 return false;
638 }
639 }
640
641 if (m_memberMgr.getSize() < ((isLFGGroup() || isBGGroup()) ? 1u : 2u))
642 Disband();
643
644 return true;
645 }
646 // If group size before player removal <= 2 then disband it
647 else
648 {
649 Disband();
650 return false;
651 }
652}
653
654void Group::ChangeLeader(ObjectGuid newLeaderGuid, int8 partyIndex)
655{
656 member_witerator slot = _getMemberWSlot(newLeaderGuid);
657
658 if (slot == m_memberSlots.end())
659 return;
660
661 Player* newLeader = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(slot->guid);
662
663 // Don't allow switching leader to offline players
664 if (!newLeader)
665 return;
666
667 sScriptMgr->OnGroupChangeLeader(this, newLeaderGuid, m_leaderGuid);
668
669 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
670 {
671 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
672
673 // Remove the groups permanent instance bindings
674 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_DIFFICULTY; ++i)
675 {
676 for (BoundInstancesMap::iterator itr = m_boundInstances[i].begin(); itr != m_boundInstances[i].end();)
677 {
678 // Do not unbind saves of instances that already had map created (a newLeader entered)
679 // forcing a new instance with another leader requires group disbanding (confirmed on retail)
680 if (itr->second.perm && !sMapMgr->FindMap(itr->first, itr->second.save->GetInstanceId()))
681 {
682 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP_INSTANCE_PERM_BINDING);
683 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
684 stmt->setUInt32(1, itr->second.save->GetInstanceId());
685 trans->Append(stmt);
686
687 itr->second.save->RemoveGroup(this);
688 m_boundInstances[i].erase(itr++);
689 }
690 else
691 ++itr;
692 }
693 }
694
695 // Copy the permanent binds from the new leader to the group
696 Player::ConvertInstancesToGroup(newLeader, this, true);
697
698 // Update the group leader
699 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_LEADER);
700
701 stmt->setUInt64(0, newLeader->GetGUID().GetCounter());
702 stmt->setUInt32(1, m_dbStoreId);
703
704 trans->Append(stmt);
705
706 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
707 }
708
709 if (Player* oldLeader = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(m_leaderGuid))
710 oldLeader->RemoveFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GROUP_LEADER);
711
712 newLeader->SetFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_FLAGS_GROUP_LEADER);
713 m_leaderGuid = newLeader->GetGUID();
714 m_leaderName = newLeader->GetName();
715 ToggleGroupMemberFlag(slot, MEMBER_FLAG_ASSISTANT, false);
716
717 WorldPackets::Party::GroupNewLeader groupNewLeader;
718 groupNewLeader.Name = m_leaderName;
719 groupNewLeader.PartyIndex = partyIndex;
720 BroadcastPacket(groupNewLeader.Write(), true);
721}
722
723void Group::Disband(bool hideDestroy /* = false */)
724{
725 sScriptMgr->OnGroupDisband(this);
726
727 Player* player;
728 for (member_citerator citr = m_memberSlots.begin(); citr != m_memberSlots.end(); ++citr)
729 {
730 player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(citr->guid);
731 if (!player)
732 continue;
733
734 //we cannot call _removeMember because it would invalidate member iterator
735 //if we are removing player from battleground raid
736 if (isBGGroup() || isBFGroup())
737 player->RemoveFromBattlegroundOrBattlefieldRaid();
738 else
739 {
740 //we can remove player who is in battleground from his original group
741 if (player->GetOriginalGroup() == this)
742 player->SetOriginalGroup(NULL);
743 else
744 player->SetGroup(NULL);
745 }
746
747 // quest related GO state dependent from raid membership
748 if (isRaidGroup())
749 player->UpdateForQuestWorldObjects();
750
751 if (!player->GetSession())
752 continue;
753
754 WorldPacket data;
755 if (!hideDestroy)
756 {
757 data.Initialize(SMSG_GROUP_DESTROYED, 0);
758 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
759 }
760
761 //we already removed player from group and in player->GetGroup() is his original group, send update
762 if (Group* group = player->GetGroup())
763 {
764 group->SendUpdate();
765 }
766 else
767 {
768 data.Initialize(SMSG_PARTY_UPDATE, 1+1+1+1+8+4+4+8);
769 data << uint8(0x10) << uint8(0) << uint8(0) << uint8(0);
770 data << m_guid << uint32(m_counter) << uint32(0) << uint64(0);
771 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
772 }
773
774 _homebindIfInstance(player);
775 }
776 RollId.clear();
777 m_memberSlots.clear();
778
779 RemoveAllInvites();
780
781 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
782 {
783 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
784
785 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP);
786 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
787 trans->Append(stmt);
788
789 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP_MEMBER_ALL);
790 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
791 trans->Append(stmt);
792
793 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
794
795 ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND, false, false, NULL);
796 ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND, true, false, NULL);
797 ResetInstances(INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND, true, true, NULL);
798
799 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_LFG_DATA);
800 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
801 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
802
803 sGroupMgr->FreeGroupDbStoreId(this);
804 }
805
806 sGroupMgr->RemoveGroup(this);
807 delete this;
808}

814void Group::SendLootStartRoll(uint32 countDown, uint32 mapid, const Roll &r)
815{
816 WorldPacket data(SMSG_START_LOOT_ROLL, (8+4+4+4+4+4+4+1));
817 data << r.itemGUID; // guid of rolled item
818 data << uint32(mapid); // 3.3.3 mapid
819 data << uint32(r.itemSlot); // itemslot
820 data << uint32(r.itemid); // the itemEntryId for the item that shall be rolled for
821 data << uint32(r.itemRandomSuffix); // randomSuffix
822 data << uint32(r.itemRandomPropId); // item random property ID
823 data << uint32(r.itemCount); // items in stack
824 data << uint32(countDown); // the countdown time to choose "need" or "greed"
825 data << uint8(r.rollVoteMask); // roll type mask
826 data << uint8(r.totalPlayersRolling); // maybe the number of players rolling for it???
827
828 for (Roll::PlayerVote::const_iterator itr=r.playerVote.begin(); itr != r.playerVote.end(); ++itr)
829 {
830 Player* p = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(itr->first);
831 if (!p || !p->GetSession())
832 continue;
833
834 if (itr->second == NOT_EMITED_YET)
835 p->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
836 }
837}

947void Group::GroupLoot(Loot* loot, WorldObject* pLootedObject)
948{
949 std::vector<LootItem>::iterator i;
950 ItemTemplate const* item;
951 uint8 itemSlot = 0;
952
953 for (i = loot->items.begin(); i != loot->items.end(); ++i, ++itemSlot)
954 {
955 if (i->freeforall)
956 continue;
957
958 item = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(i->itemid);
959 if (!item)
960 {
961 //TC_LOG_DEBUG("misc", "Group::GroupLoot: missing item prototype for item with id: %d", i->itemid);
962 continue;
963 }
964
965 //roll for over-threshold item if it's one-player loot
966 if (item->GetQuality() >= uint32(m_lootThreshold))
967 {
968 ObjectGuid newitemGUID = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Item>(sObjectMgr->GetGenerator<HighGuid::Item>().Generate());
969 Roll* r = new Roll(newitemGUID, *i);
970
971 //a vector is filled with only near party members
972 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
973 {
974 Player* member = itr->GetSource();
975 if (!member || !member->GetSession())
976 continue;
977 if (i->AllowedForPlayer(member))
978 {
979 if (member->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
980 {
981 r->totalPlayersRolling++;
982
983 if (member->GetPassOnGroupLoot())
984 {
985 r->playerVote[member->GetGUID()] = PASS;
986 r->totalPass++;
987 // can't broadcast the pass now. need to wait until all rolling players are known.
988 }
989 else
990 r->playerVote[member->GetGUID()] = NOT_EMITED_YET;
991 }
992 }
993 }
994
995 if (r->totalPlayersRolling > 0)
996 {
997 r->setLoot(loot);
998 r->itemSlot = itemSlot;
999 if (item->DisenchantID && m_maxEnchantingLevel >= item->RequiredDisenchantSkill)
1000 r->rollVoteMask |= ROLL_FLAG_TYPE_DISENCHANT;
1001
1002 loot->items[itemSlot].is_blocked = true;
1003
1004 // If there is any "auto pass", broadcast the pass now.
1005 if (r->totalPass)
1006 {
1007 for (Roll::PlayerVote::const_iterator itr=r->playerVote.begin(); itr != r->playerVote.end(); ++itr)
1008 {
1009 Player* p = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(itr->first);
1010 if (!p || !p->GetSession())
1011 continue;
1012
1013 if (itr->second == PASS)
1014 SendLootRoll(newitemGUID, p->GetGUID(), 128, ROLL_PASS, *r);
1015 }
1016 }
1017
1018 SendLootStartRoll(60000, pLootedObject->GetMapId(), *r);
1019
1020 RollId.push_back(r);
1021
1022 if (Creature* creature = pLootedObject->ToCreature())
1023 {
1024 creature->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1025 creature->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1026 }
1027 else if (GameObject* go = pLootedObject->ToGameObject())
1028 {
1029 go->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1030 go->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1031 }
1032 }
1033 else
1034 delete r;
1035 }
1036 else
1037 i->is_underthreshold = true;
1038 }
1039
1040 for (i = loot->quest_items.begin(); i != loot->quest_items.end(); ++i, ++itemSlot)
1041 {
1042 if (!i->follow_loot_rules)
1043 continue;
1044
1045 item = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(i->itemid);
1046 if (!item)
1047 {
1048 //TC_LOG_DEBUG("misc", "Group::GroupLoot: missing item prototype for item with id: %d", i->itemid);
1049 continue;
1050 }
1051
1052 ObjectGuid newitemGUID = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Item>(sObjectMgr->GetGenerator<HighGuid::Item>().Generate());
1053 Roll* r = new Roll(newitemGUID, *i);
1054
1055 //a vector is filled with only near party members
1056 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
1057 {
1058 Player* member = itr->GetSource();
1059 if (!member || !member->GetSession())
1060 continue;
1061
1062 if (i->AllowedForPlayer(member))
1063 {
1064 if (member->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1065 {
1066 r->totalPlayersRolling++;
1067 r->playerVote[member->GetGUID()] = NOT_EMITED_YET;
1068 }
1069 }
1070 }
1071
1072 if (r->totalPlayersRolling > 0)
1073 {
1074 r->setLoot(loot);
1075 r->itemSlot = itemSlot;
1076
1077 loot->quest_items[itemSlot - loot->items.size()].is_blocked = true;
1078
1079 SendLootStartRoll(60000, pLootedObject->GetMapId(), *r);
1080
1081 RollId.push_back(r);
1082
1083 if (Creature* creature = pLootedObject->ToCreature())
1084 {
1085 creature->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1086 creature->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1087 }
1088 else if (GameObject* go = pLootedObject->ToGameObject())
1089 {
1090 go->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1091 go->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1092 }
1093 }
1094 else
1095 delete r;
1096 }
1097}

1100{
1101 ItemTemplate const* item;
1102 uint8 itemSlot = 0;
1103 for (std::vector<LootItem>::iterator i = loot->items.begin(); i != loot->items.end(); ++i, ++itemSlot)
1104 {
1105 if (i->freeforall)
1106 continue;
1107
1108 item = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(i->itemid);
1109

1124 {
1125 r->totalPlayersRolling++;

1161

1166 creature->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1167 creature->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1168 }
1169 else if (GameObject* go = lootedObject->ToGameObject())
1170 {
1171 go->m_groupLootTimer = 60000;
1172 go->lootingGroupLowGUID = GetGUID();
1173 }
1174 }
1175 else
1176 delete r;
1177 }
1178 else
1179 i->is_underthreshold = true;
1180 }
1181
1182 for (std::vector<LootItem>::iterator i = loot->quest_items.begin(); i != loot->quest_items.end(); ++i, ++itemSlot)
1183 {
1184 if (!i->follow_loot_rules)
1185 continue;
1186
1187 item = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(i->itemid);
1188 ObjectGuid newitemGUID = ObjectGuid::Create<HighGuid::Item>(sObjectMgr->GetGenerator<HighGuid::Item>().Generate());
1189 Roll* r = new Roll(newitemGUID, *i);
1190
1191 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
1192 {
1193 Player* playerToRoll = itr->GetSource();
1194 if (!playerToRoll || !playerToRoll->GetSession())

1243void Group::MasterLoot(Loot* loot, WorldObject* pLootedObject)
1244{
1245 TC_LOG_DEBUG("network", "Group::MasterLoot (SMSG_MASTER_LOOT_CANDIDATE_LIST)");
1246
1247 for (std::vector<LootItem>::iterator i = loot->items.begin(); i != loot->items.end(); ++i)
1248 {
1249 if (i->freeforall)
1250 continue;
1251
1252 i->is_blocked = !i->is_underthreshold;
1253 }
1254
1255 for (std::vector<LootItem>::iterator i = loot->quest_items.begin(); i != loot->quest_items.end(); ++i)
1256 {
1257 if (!i->follow_loot_rules)
1258 continue;
1259
1260 i->is_blocked = !i->is_underthreshold;
1261 }
1262
1263 uint32 real_count = 0;
1264
1265 WorldPacket data(SMSG_MASTER_LOOT_CANDIDATE_LIST, 1 + GetMembersCount() * 8);
1266 data << uint8(GetMembersCount());
1267
1268 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
1269 {
1270 Player* looter = itr->GetSource();
1271 if (!looter->IsInWorld())
1272 continue;
1273
1274 if (looter->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1275 {
1276 data << looter->GetGUID();
1277 ++real_count;
1278 }
1279 }
1280
1281 data.put<uint8>(0, real_count);
1282
1283 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next())
1284 {
1285 Player* looter = itr->GetSource();
1286 if (looter->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1287 looter->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
1288 }
1289}
1290
1291void Group::CountRollVote(ObjectGuid playerGUID, ObjectGuid Guid, uint8 Choice)
1292{
1293 Rolls::iterator rollI = GetRoll(Guid);
1294 if (rollI == RollId.end())
1295 return;
1296 Roll* roll = *rollI;
1297
1298 Roll::PlayerVote::iterator itr = roll->playerVote.find(playerGUID);
1299 // this condition means that player joins to the party after roll begins
1300 if (itr == roll->playerVote.end())
1301 return;
1302
1303 if (roll->getLoot())
1304 if (roll->getLoot()->items.empty())
1305 return;
1306
1307 switch (Choice)
1308 {
1309 case ROLL_PASS: // Player choose pass
1310 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, playerGUID, 128, ROLL_PASS, *roll);
1311 ++roll->totalPass;
1312 itr->second = PASS;
1313 break;
1314 case ROLL_NEED: // player choose Need
1315 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, playerGUID, 0, 0, *roll);
1316 ++roll->totalNeed;
1317 itr->second = NEED;
1318 break;
1319 case ROLL_GREED: // player choose Greed
1320 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, playerGUID, 128, ROLL_GREED, *roll);
1321 ++roll->totalGreed;
1322 itr->second = GREED;
1323 break;
1324 case ROLL_DISENCHANT: // player choose Disenchant
1325 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, playerGUID, 128, ROLL_DISENCHANT, *roll);
1326 ++roll->totalGreed;
1327 itr->second = DISENCHANT;
1328 break;
1329 }
1330
1331 if (roll->totalPass + roll->totalNeed + roll->totalGreed >= roll->totalPlayersRolling)
1332 CountTheRoll(rollI);
1333}

1335//called when roll timer expires
1336void Group::EndRoll(Loot* pLoot)

1348
1349void Group::CountTheRoll(Rolls::iterator rollI)
1350{
1351 Roll* roll = *rollI;
1352 if (!roll->isValid()) // is loot already deleted ?
1353 {
1354 RollId.erase(rollI);
1355 delete roll;
1356 return;
1357 }
1358
1359 //end of the roll
1360 if (roll->totalNeed > 0)
1361 {
1362 if (!roll->playerVote.empty())
1363 {
1364 uint8 maxresul = 0;
1365 ObjectGuid maxguid = (*roll->playerVote.begin()).first;
1366 Player* player;
1367
1368 for (Roll::PlayerVote::const_iterator itr=roll->playerVote.begin(); itr != roll->playerVote.end(); ++itr)
1369 {
1370 if (itr->second != NEED)
1371 continue;
1372
1373 uint8 randomN = urand(1, 100);
1374 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, itr->first, randomN, ROLL_NEED, *roll);
1375 if (maxresul < randomN)
1376 {
1377 maxguid = itr->first;
1378 maxresul = randomN;
1379 }
1380 }
1381 SendLootRollWon(ObjectGuid::Empty, maxguid, maxresul, ROLL_NEED, *roll);
1382 player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(maxguid);
1383
1384 if (player && player->GetSession())
1385 {
1386 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_ROLL_NEED_ON_LOOT, roll->itemid, maxresul);
1387
1388 ItemPosCountVec dest;
1389 LootItem* item = &(roll->itemSlot >= roll->getLoot()->items.size() ? roll->getLoot()->quest_items[roll->itemSlot - roll->getLoot()->items.size()] : roll->getLoot()->items[roll->itemSlot]);
1390 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, roll->itemid, item->count);
1391 if (msg == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1392 {
1393 item->is_looted = true;
1394 roll->getLoot()->NotifyItemRemoved(roll->itemSlot);
1395 roll->getLoot()->unlootedCount--;
1396 player->StoreNewItem(dest, roll->itemid, true, item->randomPropertyId, item->GetAllowedLooters(), item->BonusListIDs);
1397 }
1398 else
1399 {
1400 item->is_blocked = false;
1401 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, roll->itemid);
1402 }
1403 }
1404 }
1405 }
1406 else if (roll->totalGreed > 0)
1407 {
1408 if (!roll->playerVote.empty())
1409 {
1410 uint8 maxresul = 0;
1411 ObjectGuid maxguid = (*roll->playerVote.begin()).first;
1412 Player* player;
1413 RollVote rollvote = NOT_VALID;
1414
1415 Roll::PlayerVote::iterator itr;
1416 for (itr = roll->playerVote.begin(); itr != roll->playerVote.end(); ++itr)
1417 {
1418 if (itr->second != GREED && itr->second != DISENCHANT)
1419 continue;
1420
1421 uint8 randomN = urand(1, 100);
1422 SendLootRoll(ObjectGuid::Empty, itr->first, randomN, itr->second, *roll);
1423 if (maxresul < randomN)
1424 {
1425 maxguid = itr->first;
1426 maxresul = randomN;
1427 rollvote = itr->second;
1428 }
1429 }
1430 SendLootRollWon(ObjectGuid::Empty, maxguid, maxresul, rollvote, *roll);
1431 player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(maxguid);
1432
1433 if (player && player->GetSession())
1434 {
1435 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_ROLL_GREED_ON_LOOT, roll->itemid, maxresul);
1436
1437 LootItem* item = &(roll->itemSlot >= roll->getLoot()->items.size() ? roll->getLoot()->quest_items[roll->itemSlot - roll->getLoot()->items.size()] : roll->getLoot()->items[roll->itemSlot]);
1438
1439 if (rollvote == GREED)
1440 {
1441 ItemPosCountVec dest;
1442 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, roll->itemid, item->count);
1443 if (msg == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1444 {
1445 item->is_looted = true;
1446 roll->getLoot()->NotifyItemRemoved(roll->itemSlot);
1447 roll->getLoot()->unlootedCount--;
1448 player->StoreNewItem(dest, roll->itemid, true, item->randomPropertyId, item->GetAllowedLooters(), item->BonusListIDs);
1449 }
1450 else
1451 {
1452 item->is_blocked = false;
1453 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, roll->itemid);
1454 }
1455 }
1456 else if (rollvote == DISENCHANT)
1457 {
1458 item->is_looted = true;
1459 roll->getLoot()->NotifyItemRemoved(roll->itemSlot);
1460 roll->getLoot()->unlootedCount--;
1461 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(roll->itemid);
1462 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_CAST_SPELL, 13262); // Disenchant
1463
1464 ItemPosCountVec dest;
1465 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, roll->itemid, item->count);
1466 if (msg == EQUIP_ERR_OK)
1467 player->AutoStoreLoot(pProto->DisenchantID, LootTemplates_Disenchant, true);
1468 else // If the player's inventory is full, send the disenchant result in a mail.
1469 {
1470 Loot loot;
1471 loot.FillLoot(pProto->DisenchantID, LootTemplates_Disenchant, player, true);
1472
1473 uint32 max_slot = loot.GetMaxSlotInLootFor(player);
1474 for (uint32 i = 0; i < max_slot; ++i)
1475 {
1476 LootItem* lootItem = loot.LootItemInSlot(i, player);
1477 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, lootItem->itemid);
1478 player->SendItemRetrievalMail(lootItem->itemid, lootItem->count);
1479 }
1480 }
1481 }
1482 }
1483 }
1484 }
1485 else
1486 {
1487 SendLootAllPassed(*roll);
1488
1489 // remove is_blocked so that the item is lootable by all players
1490 LootItem* item = &(roll->itemSlot >= roll->getLoot()->items.size() ? roll->getLoot()->quest_items[roll->itemSlot - roll->getLoot()->items.size()] : roll->getLoot()->items[roll->itemSlot]);
1491 if (item)
1492 item->is_blocked = false;
1493 }
1494
1495 RollId.erase(rollI);
1496 delete roll;
1497}

1711// Allows setting sub groups both for online or offline members
1712void Group::ChangeMembersGroup(ObjectGuid guid, uint8 group)
1713{
1714 // Only raid groups have sub groups
1715 if (!isRaidGroup())
1716 return;
1717
1718 // Check if player is really in the raid
1719 member_witerator slot = _getMemberWSlot(guid);
1720 if (slot == m_memberSlots.end())
1721 return;
1722
1723 uint8 prevSubGroup = slot->group;
1724 // Abort if the player is already in the target sub group
1725 if (prevSubGroup == group)
1726 return;
1727
1728 // Update the player slot with the new sub group setting
1729 slot->group = group;
1730
1731 // Increase the counter of the new sub group..
1732 SubGroupCounterIncrease(group);
1733
1734 // ..and decrease the counter of the previous one
1735 SubGroupCounterDecrease(prevSubGroup);
1736
1737 // Preserve new sub group in database for non-raid groups
1738 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
1739 {
1740 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_MEMBER_SUBGROUP);
1741
1742 stmt->setUInt8(0, group);
1743 stmt->setUInt64(1, guid.GetCounter());
1744
1745 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
1746 }
1747
1748 // In case the moved player is online, update the player object with the new sub group references
1749 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(guid))
1750 {
1751 if (player->GetGroup() == this)
1752 player->GetGroupRef().setSubGroup(group);
1753 else
1754 {
1755 // If player is in BG raid, it is possible that he is also in normal raid - and that normal raid is stored in m_originalGroup reference
1756 player->GetOriginalGroupRef().setSubGroup(group);
1757 }
1758 }
1759
1760 // Broadcast the changes to the group
1761 SendUpdate();
1762}
1763
1764void Group::SwapMembersGroups(ObjectGuid firstGuid, ObjectGuid secondGuid)
1765{
1766 if (!isRaidGroup())
1767 return;
1768
1769 member_witerator slots[2];
1770 slots[0] = _getMemberWSlot(firstGuid);
1771 slots[1] = _getMemberWSlot(secondGuid);
1772 if (slots[0] == m_memberSlots.end() || slots[1] == m_memberSlots.end())
1773 return;
1774
1775 if (slots[0]->group == slots[1]->group)
1776 return;
1777
1778 uint8 tmp = slots[0]->group;
1779 slots[0]->group = slots[1]->group;
1780 slots[1]->group = tmp;
1781
1782 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1783 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; i++)
1784 {
1785 // Preserve new sub group in database for non-raid groups
1786 if (!isBGGroup() && !isBFGroup())
1787 {
1788 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_MEMBER_SUBGROUP);
1789
1790 stmt->setUInt8(0, slots[i]->group);
1791 stmt->setUInt64(1, slots[i]->guid.GetCounter());
1792
1793 trans->Append(stmt);
1794 }
1795
1796 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(slots[i]->guid))
1797 {
1798 if (player->GetGroup() == this)
1799 player->GetGroupRef().setSubGroup(slots[i]->group);
1800 else
1801 player->GetOriginalGroupRef().setSubGroup(slots[i]->group);
1802 }
1803 }
1804 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
1805
1806 SendUpdate();
1807}
1808
1809// Retrieve the next Round-Roubin player for the group
1810//
1811// No update done if loot method is FFA.
1812//
1813// If the RR player is not yet set for the group, the first group member becomes the round-robin player.
1814// If the RR player is set, the next player in group becomes the round-robin player.
1815//
1816// If ifneed is true,
1817// the current RR player is checked to be near the looted object.
1818// if yes, no update done.
1819// if not, he loses his turn.
1820void Group::UpdateLooterGuid(WorldObject* pLootedObject, bool ifneed)
1821{
1822 // round robin style looting applies for all low
1823 // quality items in each loot method except free for all
1824 if (GetLootMethod() == FREE_FOR_ALL)
1825 return;
1826
1827 ObjectGuid oldLooterGUID = GetLooterGuid();
1828 member_citerator guid_itr = _getMemberCSlot(oldLooterGUID);
1829 if (guid_itr != m_memberSlots.end())
1830 {
1831 if (ifneed)
1832 {
1833 // not update if only update if need and ok
1834 Player* looter = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(guid_itr->guid);
1835 if (looter && looter->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1836 return;
1837 }
1838 ++guid_itr;
1839 }
1840
1841 // search next after current
1842 Player* pNewLooter = NULL;
1843 for (member_citerator itr = guid_itr; itr != m_memberSlots.end(); ++itr)
1844 {
1845 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(itr->guid))
1846 if (player->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1847 {
1848 pNewLooter = player;
1849 break;
1850 }
1851 }
1852
1853 if (!pNewLooter)
1854 {
1855 // search from start
1856 for (member_citerator itr = m_memberSlots.begin(); itr != guid_itr; ++itr)
1857 {
1858 if (Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(itr->guid))
1859 if (player->IsAtGroupRewardDistance(pLootedObject))
1860 {
1861 pNewLooter = player;
1862 break;
1863 }
1864 }
1865 }
1866
1867 if (pNewLooter)
1868 {
1869 if (oldLooterGUID != pNewLooter->GetGUID())
1870 {
1871 SetLooterGuid(pNewLooter->GetGUID());
1872 SendUpdate();
1873 }
1874 }
1875 else
1876 {
1877 SetLooterGuid(ObjectGuid::Empty);
1878 SendUpdate();
1879 }
1880}
1881
1882GroupJoinBattlegroundResult Group::CanJoinBattlegroundQueue(Battleground const* bgOrTemplate, BattlegroundQueueTypeId bgQueueTypeId, uint32 MinPlayerCount, uint32 /*MaxPlayerCount*/, bool isRated, uint32 arenaSlot, ObjectGuid& errorGuid)
1883{
1884 // check if this group is LFG group
1885 if (isLFGGroup())
1886 return ERR_LFG_CANT_USE_BATTLEGROUND;
1887
1888 BattlemasterListEntry const* bgEntry = sBattlemasterListStore.LookupEntry(bgOrTemplate->GetTypeID());
1889 if (!bgEntry)
1890 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED; // shouldn't happen
1891
1892 // check for min / max count
1893 uint32 memberscount = GetMembersCount();
1894
1895 if (memberscount > bgEntry->MaxGroupSize) // no MinPlayerCount for battlegrounds
1896 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_NONE; // ERR_GROUP_JOIN_BATTLEGROUND_TOO_MANY handled on client side
1897
1898 // get a player as reference, to compare other players' stats to (arena team id, queue id based on level, etc.)
1899 Player* reference = ASSERT_NOTNULL(GetFirstMember())->GetSource();
1900 // no reference found, can't join this way
1901 if (!reference)
1902 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED;
1903
1904 PvPDifficultyEntry const* bracketEntry = GetBattlegroundBracketByLevel(bgOrTemplate->GetMapId(), reference->getLevel());
1905 if (!bracketEntry)
1906 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED;
1907
1908 uint32 arenaTeamId = reference->GetArenaTeamId(arenaSlot);
1909 uint32 team = reference->GetTeam();
1910
1911 BattlegroundQueueTypeId bgQueueTypeIdRandom = BattlegroundMgr::BGQueueTypeId(BATTLEGROUND_RB, 0);
1912
1913 // check every member of the group to be able to join
1914 memberscount = 0;
1915 for (GroupReference* itr = GetFirstMember(); itr != NULL; itr = itr->next(), ++memberscount)
1916 {
1917 Player* member = itr->GetSource();
1918 // offline member? don't let join
1919 if (!member)
1920 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED;
1921 // don't allow cross-faction join as group
1922 if (member->GetTeam() != team)
1923 {
1924 errorGuid = member->GetGUID();
1925 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_TIMED_OUT;
1926 }
1927 // not in the same battleground level braket, don't let join
1928 PvPDifficultyEntry const* memberBracketEntry = GetBattlegroundBracketByLevel(bracketEntry->MapID, member->getLevel());
1929 if (memberBracketEntry != bracketEntry)
1930 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_RANGE_INDEX;
1931 // don't let join rated matches if the arena team id doesn't match
1932 if (isRated && member->GetArenaTeamId(arenaSlot) != arenaTeamId)
1933 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED;
1934 // don't let join if someone from the group is already in that bg queue
1935 if (member->InBattlegroundQueueForBattlegroundQueueType(bgQueueTypeId))
1936 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED; // not blizz-like
1937 // don't let join if someone from the group is in bg queue random
1938 if (member->InBattlegroundQueueForBattlegroundQueueType(bgQueueTypeIdRandom))
1939 return ERR_IN_RANDOM_BG;
1940 // don't let join to bg queue random if someone from the group is already in bg queue
1941 if (bgOrTemplate->GetTypeID() == BATTLEGROUND_RB && member->InBattlegroundQueue())
1942 return ERR_IN_NON_RANDOM_BG;
1943 // check for deserter debuff in case not arena queue
1944 if (bgOrTemplate->GetTypeID() != BATTLEGROUND_AA && !member->CanJoinToBattleground(bgOrTemplate))
1945 return ERR_GROUP_JOIN_BATTLEGROUND_DESERTERS;
1946 // check if member can join any more battleground queues
1947 if (!member->HasFreeBattlegroundQueueId())
1948 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_TOO_MANY_QUEUES; // not blizz-like
1949 // check if someone in party is using dungeon system
1950 if (member->isUsingLfg())
1951 return ERR_LFG_CANT_USE_BATTLEGROUND;
1952 // check Freeze debuff
1953 if (member->HasAura(9454))
1954 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_JOIN_FAILED;
1955 }
1956
1957 // only check for MinPlayerCount since MinPlayerCount == MaxPlayerCount for arenas...
1958 if (bgOrTemplate->isArena() && memberscount != MinPlayerCount)
1959 return ERR_ARENA_TEAM_PARTY_SIZE;
1960
1961 return ERR_BATTLEGROUND_NONE;
1962}

2062void Group::ResetInstances(uint8 method, bool isRaid, bool isLegacy, Player* SendMsgTo)
2063{
2064 if (isBGGroup() || isBFGroup())
2065 return;
2066
2067 // method can be INSTANCE_RESET_ALL, INSTANCE_RESET_CHANGE_DIFFICULTY, INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND
2068
2069 // we assume that when the difficulty changes, all instances that can be reset will be
2070 Difficulty diff = GetDungeonDifficultyID();
2071 if (isRaid)
2072 {
2073 if (!isLegacy)
2074 diff = GetRaidDifficultyID();
2075 else
2076 diff = GetLegacyRaidDifficultyID();
2077 }
2078
2079 for (BoundInstancesMap::iterator itr = m_boundInstances[diff].begin(); itr != m_boundInstances[diff].end();)
2080 {
2081 InstanceSave* instanceSave = itr->second.save;
2082 const MapEntry* entry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(itr->first);
2083 if (!entry || entry->IsRaid() != isRaid || (!instanceSave->CanReset() && method != INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND))
2084 {
2085 ++itr;
2086 continue;
2087 }
2088
2089 if (method == INSTANCE_RESET_ALL)
2090 {
2091 // the "reset all instances" method can only reset normal maps
2092 if (entry->IsRaid() || diff == DIFFICULTY_HEROIC)
2093 {
2094 ++itr;
2095 continue;
2096 }
2097 }
2098
2099 bool isEmpty = true;
2100 // if the map is loaded, reset it
2101 Map* map = sMapMgr->FindMap(instanceSave->GetMapId(), instanceSave->GetInstanceId());
2102 if (map && map->IsDungeon() && !(method == INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND && !instanceSave->CanReset()))
2103 {
2104 if (instanceSave->CanReset())
2105 isEmpty = ((InstanceMap*)map)->Reset(method);
2106 else
2107 isEmpty = !map->HavePlayers();
2108 }
2109
2110 if (SendMsgTo)
2111 {
2112 if (!isEmpty)
2113 SendMsgTo->SendResetInstanceFailed(INSTANCE_RESET_FAILED, instanceSave->GetMapId());
2114 else if (sWorld->getBoolConfig(CONFIG_INSTANCES_RESET_ANNOUNCE))
2115 {
2116 if (Group* group = SendMsgTo->GetGroup())
2117 {
2118 for (GroupReference* groupRef = group->GetFirstMember(); groupRef != NULL; groupRef = groupRef->next())
2119 if (Player* player = groupRef->GetSource())
2120 player->SendResetInstanceSuccess(instanceSave->GetMapId());
2121 }
2122
2123 else
2124 SendMsgTo->SendResetInstanceSuccess(instanceSave->GetMapId());
2125 }
2126 else
2127 SendMsgTo->SendResetInstanceSuccess(instanceSave->GetMapId());
2128 }
2129
2130 if (isEmpty || method == INSTANCE_RESET_GROUP_DISBAND || method == INSTANCE_RESET_CHANGE_DIFFICULTY)
2131 {
2132 // do not reset the instance, just unbind if others are permanently bound to it
2133 if (isEmpty && instanceSave->CanReset())
2134 instanceSave->DeleteFromDB();
2135 else
2136 {
2137 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GROUP_INSTANCE_BY_INSTANCE);
2138
2139 stmt->setUInt32(0, instanceSave->GetInstanceId());
2140
2141 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
2142 }
2143
2144
2145 // i don't know for sure if hash_map iterators
2146 m_boundInstances[diff].erase(itr);
2147 itr = m_boundInstances[diff].begin();
2148 // this unloads the instance save unless online players are bound to it
2149 // (eg. permanent binds or GM solo binds)
2150 instanceSave->RemoveGroup(this);
2151 }
2152 else
2153 ++itr;
2154 }
2155}

2190InstanceGroupBind* Group::BindToInstance(InstanceSave* save, bool permanent, bool load)
2191{
2192 if (!save || isBGGroup() || isBFGroup())
2193 return NULL;
2194
2195 InstanceGroupBind& bind = m_boundInstances[save->GetDifficultyID()][save->GetMapId()];
2196 if (!load && (!bind.save || permanent != bind.perm || save != bind.save))
2197 {
2198 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_REP_GROUP_INSTANCE);
2199
2200 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_dbStoreId);
2201 stmt->setUInt32(1, save->GetInstanceId());
2202 stmt->setBool(2, permanent);
2203
2204 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
2205 }
2206
2207 if (bind.save != save)
2208 {
2209 if (bind.save)
2210 bind.save->RemoveGroup(this);
2211 save->AddGroup(this);
2212 }
2213
2214 bind.save = save;
2215 bind.perm = permanent;
2216 if (!load)
2217 TC_LOG_DEBUG("maps", "Group::BindToInstance: %s, storage id: %u is now bound to map %d, instance %d, difficulty %d",
2218 GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), m_dbStoreId, save->GetMapId(), save->GetInstanceId(), save->GetDifficultyID());
2219
2220 return &bind;
2221}

2331void Group::StartReadyCheck(ObjectGuid starterGuid, int8 partyIndex, uint32 duration)
2332{
2333 if (m_readyCheckStarted)
2334 return;
2335
2336 member_witerator slot = _getMemberWSlot(starterGuid);
2337 if (slot == m_memberSlots.end())
2338 return ;
2339
2340 m_readyCheckStarted = true;
2341 m_readyCheckTimer = duration;
2342
2343 SetOfflineMembersReadyChecked();
2344
2345 SetMemberReadyChecked(&(*slot));
2346
2347 WorldPackets::Party::ReadyCheckStarted readyCheckStarted;
2348 readyCheckStarted.PartyGUID = m_guid;
2349 readyCheckStarted.PartyIndex = partyIndex;
2350 readyCheckStarted.InitiatorGUID = starterGuid;
2351 readyCheckStarted.Duration = duration;
2352 BroadcastPacket(readyCheckStarted.Write(), false);
2353}

2355void Group::EndReadyCheck(void)
2356{
2357 if (!m_readyCheckStarted)
2358 return;
2359
2360 m_readyCheckStarted = false;
2361 m_readyCheckTimer = 0;
2362
2363 ResetMemberReadyChecked();
2364
2365 WorldPackets::Party::ReadyCheckCompleted readyCheckCompleted;
2366 readyCheckCompleted.PartyIndex = 0;
2367 readyCheckCompleted.PartyGUID = m_guid;
2368 BroadcastPacket(readyCheckCompleted.Write(), false);
2369}

2423void Group::AddRaidMarker(uint8 markerId, uint32 mapId, float positionX, float positionY, float positionZ, ObjectGuid transportGuid)
2424{
2425 if (markerId >= RAID_MARKERS_COUNT || m_markers[markerId])
2426 return;
2427
2428 m_activeMarkers |= (1 << markerId);
2429 m_markers[markerId] = Trinity::make_unique<RaidMarker>(mapId, positionX, positionY, positionZ, transportGuid);
2430 SendRaidMarkersChanged();
2431}
2432
2433void Group::DeleteRaidMarker(uint8 markerId)
2434{
2435 if (markerId > RAID_MARKERS_COUNT)
2436 return;
2437
2438 for (uint8 i = 0; i < RAID_MARKERS_COUNT; i++)
2439 if (m_markers[i] && (markerId == i || markerId == RAID_MARKERS_COUNT))
2440 {
2441 m_markers[i] = nullptr;
2442 m_activeMarkers &= ~(1 << i);
2443 }
2444
2445 SendRaidMarkersChanged();
2446}
2447
2448void Group::SendRaidMarkersChanged(WorldSession* session, int8 partyIndex)
2449{
2450 WorldPackets::Party::RaidMarkersChanged packet;
2451
2452 packet.PartyIndex = partyIndex;
2453 packet.ActiveMarkers = m_activeMarkers;
2454
2455 for (uint8 i = 0; i < RAID_MARKERS_COUNT; i++)
2456 if (m_markers[i])
2457 packet.RaidMarkers.push_back(m_markers[i].get());
2458
2459 if (session)
2460 session->SendPacket(packet.Write());
2461 else
2462 BroadcastPacket(packet.Write(), false);
2463}

2595void Group::SetGroupMemberFlag(ObjectGuid guid, bool apply, GroupMemberFlags flag)
2596{
2597 // Assistants, main assistants and main tanks are only available in raid groups
2598 if (!isRaidGroup())
2599 return;
2600
2601 // Check if player is really in the raid
2602 member_witerator slot = _getMemberWSlot(guid);
2603 if (slot == m_memberSlots.end())
2604 return;
2605
2606 // Do flag specific actions, e.g ensure uniqueness
2607 switch (flag) {
2608 case MEMBER_FLAG_MAINASSIST:
2609 RemoveUniqueGroupMemberFlag(MEMBER_FLAG_MAINASSIST); // Remove main assist flag from current if any.
2610 break;
2611 case MEMBER_FLAG_MAINTANK:
2612 RemoveUniqueGroupMemberFlag(MEMBER_FLAG_MAINTANK); // Remove main tank flag from current if any.
2613 break;
2614 case MEMBER_FLAG_ASSISTANT:
2615 break;
2616 default:
2617 return; // This should never happen
2618 }
2619
2620 // Switch the actual flag
2621 ToggleGroupMemberFlag(slot, flag, apply);
2622
2623 // Preserve the new setting in the db
2624 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_UPD_GROUP_MEMBER_FLAG);
2625
2626 stmt->setUInt8(0, slot->flags);
2627 stmt->setUInt64(1, guid.GetCounter());
2628
2629 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
2630
2631 // Broadcast the changes to the group
2632 SendUpdate();
2633}
